  no_touch : Item will interact as solid instead of being picked up by player.
  hover : Item will spawn where it was placed in the map and won't drop the floor.

  -------- Radiant config --------
  model="models/powerups/quake_pentagram/tris.obj"
  */

/*QUAKED item_quake_shadows (.2 .2 .4) (-16 -16 -16) (16 16 16) triggered no_touch hover
  Ring of Shadows. Makes the player nearly invisible for 30 seconds.

  -------- Keys --------
  team : The team name for alternating item spawns.

  -------- Spawn flags --------
  triggered : Item will not appear until triggered.
  no_touch : Item will interact as solid instead of being picked up by player.
  hover : Item will spawn where it was placed in the map and won't drop the floor.

  -------- Radiant config --------
  model="models/powerups/quake_shadows/tris.obj"
  */

/*QUAKED light (0 1 0) (-8 -8 -8) (8 8 8)
 Point light source.

 -------- Keys --------
 color : Light color as 3 decimal values from 0.0 - 1.0 (default 1 1 1).
 drift : Phase offset (0-1) applied to the style animation clock. Use different values on nearby lights with the same style to prevent synchronized flickering (default 0).
 intensity : Light intensity as a positive scalar value (default 1).
 radius : Light radius in units (default 300).
 style : The light style, a string of characters a-z that modulate the light intensity over time (default 'zzz').
*/

/*QUAKED misc_dust (.8 .8 .7)
 Dust volumes emit configurable sprites, like localized weather. These are useful for creating dust, bubbles, foam, mist, etc. These are typically contents atmospheric.

 -------- Keys --------
 acceleration : The sprite acceleration (default 0 0 0).
 acceleration_spread : Per-particle random acceleration range, applied symmetrically on each axis (default 0 0 0).
 color : The sprite HSVA color as 4 decimal values (default 0 0 1 1).
 density : The sprite density (default 1).
 dir : The sprite directional axis (0 0 0 is billboard).
 end_color : The sprite HSVA end color as 4 decimal values (default 0 0 0 0).
 height : The sprite height. Setting this will cause size to be ignored (default 0).
 hz : The emission rate, in events-per-second (default 10).
 lifetime : The sprite lifetime in seconds (default 10).
 lighting : The sprite lighting scalar (default 1).
 rotation : The sprite rotation in degrees (default 0).
 rotation_spread : Per-particle random initial rotation spread from 0 to 1, where 1 is pi radians (default 0).
 rotation_velocity : The sprite rotation velocity in degrees per second (default 0).
 size : The sprite size (default 1).
 size_spread : Per-particle random size spread as a +/- fraction of size (default 0.1).
  size_acceleration : The sprite size acceleration (default 0).
  size_velocity : The sprite size velocity (default 0).
  softness : The sprite softness scalar (default 1).
  sprite : The sprite image name (default "particle1").
  velocity : The sprite velocity (default 0 0 0).
 velocity_spread : Per-particle random velocity spread, applied symmetrically on each axis (default 1 1 1).
  width : The sprite width. Setting this will cause size to be ignored (default 0).
*/

/*QUAKED misc_fireball (1 0.3 0.1) (-6 -6 -6) (6 6 6)
 Spawns an intermittent fireball that damages players. These are typically used above lava traps for ambiance.

 -------- Keys --------
 angles : The angles at which the fireball will fly (default randomized).
 dmg : The damage inflicted to entities that touch the fireball (default 4).
 random : Random time variance in seconds added to "wait" delay (default 0.5 * wait).
 speed : The speed at which the fireball will fly (default 600.0).
 wait : The interval in seconds between fireball emissions (default 5.0).
*/

/*QUAKED misc_flame (1 .7 .1) (-8 -8 -8) (8 8 8)
 Client-side flame emitter, useful for torches and ambience.

 -------- Keys --------
 density : The flame density (default 1).
 drift : The factor of randomized drift applied to the emission rate.
 hz : The emission rate, in events-per-second (default 10).
 radius : The flame radius (default 16).
 sound : The looping sound to play, or 'none' to disable (default "world/fire").
*/

/*QUAKED misc_model (.2 .4 1) (-16 -16 -16) (16 16 16)
 Client-side emission of static models (non-interactive map objects). These are useful for placing trees, torches, and other non-brush scenery.

 -------- Keys --------
 angles : The angles of orientation for the model.
 model : The static model name, e.g. trees/mytree.
 scale : The scale for a static model.
*/

/*QUAKED misc_sound (1 0 1) (-8 -8 -8) (8 8 8)
 Client-side emission of ambient sounds.

 -------- Keys --------
 drift : The factor of randomized drift applied to the emission rate.
 hz : The emission rate, in events-per-second (default 0).
 sound : The sound name, e.g. edge/wind.
*/

/*QUAKED misc_sparks (1 .6 .2) (-8 -8 -8) (8 8 8)
 Client-side emission of spark effects.

 -------- Keys --------
 angle : Sparks direction (up = -1, down = -2, yaw = positive value).
 count : The count of sparks to emit per emission (default 12).
 drift : The factor of randomized drift applied to the emission rate.
 hz : The emission rate, in events-per-second (default 0.5).
 target : The name of the entity to target to resolve the sparks direction.
*/

/*QUAKED misc_sprite (.6 .8 .6) (-8 -8 -8) (8 8 8)
 Highly configurable client-side emission of sprites. These are useful for light volumes, blood dripping from walls, or anything else you can think of. If two instances of this entity are teamed, the game will emit randomized instances that mix the properties of both teammates.

 -------- Keys --------
 acceleration : The sprite acceleration (default 0 0 0).
 color : The sprite HSVA color as 4 decimal values (default 0 0 1 1).
 count : The count of sprites to emit per emission (default 1).
 dir : The sprite directional axis (0 0 0 is billboard).
 drift : The factor of randomized drift applied to the emission rate (default 3).
 end_color : The sprite HSVA end color as 4 decimal values (default 0 0 0 0).
 height : The sprite height. Setting this will cause size to be ignored (default 0).
 hz : The emission rate, in events-per-second (default 0.5).
 lifetime : The sprite lifetime in seconds (default 10).
 lighting : The sprite lighting scalar (default 1).
 rotation : The sprite rotation in degrees (default 0).
 rotation_velocity : The sprite rotation velocity in degrees per second (default 0).
 size : The sprite size (default 1).
 size_acceleration : The sprite size acceleration (default 0).
 size_velocity : The sprite size velocity (default 0).
 softness : The sprite softness scalar (default 1).
 sprite : The sprite image name (default "particle1").
 team : The team name, for emitting randomized sprites that mix properties.
 velocity : The sprite velocity (default 0 0 0).
 width : The sprite width. Setting this will cause size to be ignored (default 0).
*/

/*QUAKED misc_steam (.8 .8 .8) (-8 -8 -8) (8 8 8)
 Client-side emission of steam effects.

 -------- Keys --------
 count : The count of sprites to emit per emission (default 1).
 drift : The factor of randomized drift applied to the emission rate (default 0.01).
 hz : The emission rate, in events-per-second (default 24).
 size : The initial sprite size (default 32).
 sound : The looping sound to play, or 'none' to disable (default "world/steam").
 target : The name of the entity to target to resolve the steam direction and velocity.
 velocity : The steam velocity (if not specified via target) (default 0 0 32).
*/

/*QUAKED misc_teleporter (1 0 0) (-32 -32 -24) (32 32 -16) no_effects
 Warps players who touch this entity to the targeted misc_teleporter_dest entity.

 -------- Keys --------
 sound : Sound to play at the teleporter and destination on use (default "misc/teleport").

 -------- Spawn flags --------
 no_effects : Suppress the default teleporter particle effects.
*/

/*QUAKED misc_teleporter_dest (1 0 0) (-32 -32 -24) (32 32 -16)
 Teleport destination for misc_teleporters.

 -------- Keys --------
 angle : Direction in which player will look when teleported.
 targetname : The target name of this entity.
*/

/*QUAKED misc_weather (.6 .7 .8)
 Weather volumes emit rain, snow, or ash particles within their brushes. These are typically contents atmospheric.

 -------- Keys --------
 density : Density multiplier for particle count (default 1.0).
 hz : Spawn rate in Hz (default 5).
 sound : Ambient sound sample (default per weather type, 'none' to disable).
 weather : Weather type: rain, snow, or ash (default "rain").
*/

/*QUAKED path_corner (.7 .3 0) (-8 -8 -8) (8 8 8) teleport no_effects
 Path corner for func_trains.

 -------- Keys --------
 pathtarget : An entity to be used by this path corner when targeted.
 target : The next corner in the path.
 targetname : The target name of this entity.

 -------- Spawn flags --------
 teleport : The path corner teleports the train as soon as it is selected.
 no_effects : Suppress the default teleport effects.
*/

/*QUAKED target_light (1 1 1) (-4 -4 -4) (4 4 4) start_on
 Emits a user-defined light when used. Lights can be chained with teams.

 -------- Keys --------
 color : The light color (default 1.0 1.0 1.0).
 radius : The radius of the light in units (default 300).
 delay : The delay before activating, in seconds (default 0).
 targetname : The target name of this entity.
 team : The team name for alternating lights.
 wait : If specified, an additional cycle will fire after this interval.

 -------- Spawn flags --------
 start_on : The light will start on.

 -------- Notes --------
 Use this entity to add switched lights. Use the wait key to synchronize
 color cycles with other entities.
*/

/*QUAKED target_speaker (1 0 0) (-8 -8 -8) (8 8 8) loop_on loop_off
 Plays a sound each time it is used, or in loop if requested.

 -------- Keys --------
 sound : The name of the sample to play, e.g. voices/haunting.
 targetname : The target name of this entity.

 -------- Spawn flags --------
 loop_on : The sound can be toggled, and will play in loop until used.
 loop_off : The sound can be toggled, and will begin playing when used.

 -------- Notes --------
 Use this entity only when a sound must be triggered by another entity. For
 ambient sounds, use the client-side version, misc_sound.
*/

/*QUAKED target_string (0 0 1) (-8 -8 -8) (8 8 8)
 Displays a center-printed message to the player when used.
 -------- KEYS --------
 message : The message to display.
 targetname : The target name of this entity.
*/

/*QUAKED trigger_always (.5 .5 .5) (-8 -8 -8) (8 8 8)
 Triggers targets once at level spawn.

 -------- Keys --------
 delay : The delay in seconds between activation and firing of targets (default 0.2).
 message : An optional message to display when this trigger fires.
 target : The name of the entity or team to use on activation.
 kill_target : The name of the entity or team to kill on activation.
*/

/*QUAKED trigger_exec (0 1 0) ?
 Executes a console command or script file when activated.

 -------- Keys --------
 command : The console command(s) to execute.
 script : The script file (.cfg) to execute.
 delay : The delay in seconds between activation and execution of the commands.
*/

/*QUAKED trigger_hurt (.5 .5 .5) ? start_off toggle ? no_protection slow
 Any player that touches this will be hurt by "dmg" points of damage every 100ms (very fast).

 -------- Keys --------
 dmg : The damage done every 100ms to any player who touches this entity (default 2).
 targetname : The target name of this entity, if it is to be triggered.

 -------- Spawn flags --------
 start_off : If set, this entity must be activated before it will hurt players.
 toggle : If set, this entity is toggled each time it is activated.
 ?
 no_protection : If set, armor will not be used to absorb damage inflicted by this entity.
 slow : Decreases the damage rate to once per second.
*/

/*QUAKED trigger_multiple (.5 .5 .5) ? triggered shootable
 Triggers multiple targets at fixed intervals.

 -------- Keys --------
 delay : Delay in seconds between activation and firing of targets (default 0).
 wait : Interval in seconds between activations (default 0.2).
 message : An optional string to display when activated.
 target : The name of the entity or team to use on activation.
 killtarget : The name of the entity or team to kill on activation.
 targetname : The target name of this entity if it is to be triggered.

 -------- Spawn flags --------
 triggered : If set, this trigger must be targeted before it will activate.
 shootable : If set, this trigger will fire when projectiles touch it.
*/

/*QUAKED trigger_once (.5 .5 .5) ? triggered
 Triggers multiple targets once.

 -------- Keys --------
 delay : Delay in seconds between activation and firing of targets (default 0).
 message : An optional string to display when activated.
 target : The name of the entity or team to use on activation.
 killtarget : The name of the entity or team to kill on activation.
 targetname : The target name of this entity if it is to be triggered.

 -------- Spawn flags --------
 triggered : If set, this trigger must be targeted before it will activate.
*/

/*QUAKED trigger_push (.5 .5 .5) ? push_once push_effects
 Pushes the player in any direction. These are commonly used to make jump pads to send the player upwards. Using the angles key, you can project the player in any direction using "pitch yaw roll."

 -------- Keys --------
 angles : The direction to push the player in "pitch yaw roll" notation (e.g. -80 270 0).
 sound : The sound effect to play when the player is pushed (default "common/jumppad").
 speed : The speed with which to push the player (default 100).

 -------- Spawn flags --------
 push_once : If set, the pusher is freed after it is used once.
 push_effects : If set, emit particle effects to indicate that a pusher is here.
*/

/*QUAKED trigger_relay (.5 .5 .5) (-8 -8 -8) (8 8 8)
 A trigger that can not be touched, but must be triggered by another entity.

 -------- Keys --------
 delay : The delay in seconds between activation and firing of targets (default 0).
 message : An optional string to display when activated.
 target : The name of the entity or team to use on activation.
 killtarget : The name of the entity or team to kill on activation.
 targetname : The target name of this entity.
*/

/*QUAKED trigger_teleporter (1 0 0) ?
 Touching this will warp players to the targeted misc_teleporter_dest entity. This is the brush form of misc_teleporter.

 -------- Keys --------
 phong : The Phong shading threshold for this model, in degrees (default 60).
 target : The target name of a misc_teleporter_dest.
*/

